The paper proposes a method for foreground segmentation using neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves training the neural networks, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of transposed convolutional networks, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the method on datasets, which involves numerical analysis and optimization, falling under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
